//You listen to the near imperceptible hum of your steeds electric engine for a bit, before turning on the solar-powered radio to tune into everyones favourite evening show.

An upbeat jingle plays before the cheery voice of the famous host and cowgirl Sally the Smoker breaks through the ether:.//

[[Continue..->SmokeSignal1]]

//After a long, silent ride through the outland praerie, Jessie "Hellrider" Allen makes camp. 

Just a days ride away from his goal, you are anxious to finally reach Purple Town. Eating a salvaged Can-O-Everything you found in a rust-speckled ruin nearby, you watch the solar panels of your electric steed, Horace, fold back into the robotic frame. //

[[Get out your radio. ->GetOutRadio]]

//The singers haunting voice fills the silence.//

[["There must be more for me out there."->WishA1]]
[["Well, goodnight.".->Goodnight Horace]]

//The song ends with the singer decades after his love has left, still waiting and hoping for her to return. Horace stares into the distance and the well-crafted face of the robotic horse-frame conveys that he is deep in thought and memory.//


[["Are you okay?" -> AreYouOkay]]

[["Nice song, but a bit too sad for my tastes." ->DialogueA1b]]

// Horace gives you long look before shaking his head, driving off a number of glowbugs.//

I apologize. That song... put me in a weird mood.

[["Want to talk about it?" ->WantToTalk?]]

//Horace stays silent.//

[[Wait for him to say something. ->LookJessie]]

[["Sorry I asked." ->SorryIAsked]]

And now it's my pleasure to present the beautiful and talented singster Tommy! More than a pretty face and a nice ass, this boy has got the voice of an angel!

//Tommys voice fills the air, singing a beautiful and haunting song about waiting for his lover to return to him."//

[["Interesting idea." ->TalkAtHoraceA0]]
